Niger State governorship standard-bearer of the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, Alh. Isah Liman Kantigi has picked Mr. Samuel Gwamna as his running mate for the 2023 general elections in the state. Kantigi unveiled his running mate today at the party secretariat in Minna, on the occasion of the presentation of certificates of return to winners of party primaries for various positions by the state chairman Bar Tanko Beji in Minna. Mr. Gwamna was one time Local Government Chairman of Tafa, Local Government Area in Niger State. The governorship candidate explained that Hon. Gwamna’s nomination was after due consultations and guidance with relevant stakeholders of the party in the state. He stated that his selection was devoid of sentiments or discrimination, but done to ensure the progress of the common man in the state. “I am ready to die for you all, I am ready to die for the common man to make sure they are protected,” Kantigi assured the party supporters. In his acceptance speech, Samuel Gwamna thanked the governorship candidate and the party for considering him worthy and competent to be running mate to Alh. Kantigi in the forthcoming elections. The state party leader, Senator Zainab Kure in her address, congratulated the candidates while urging party faithful to work hard and ensure that the PDP emerges victorious in the 2023 general elections.